---
const rawBase = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const base = rawBase.endsWith('/') ? rawBase : `${rawBase}/`;

interface Props {
  showCalculator?: boolean;
}

const { showCalculator = false } = Astro.props as Props;
---

<h2>Quick settings</h2>

<h3>Weight mode</h3>

<p><code>Weight = Dose x Ratio</code></p>

<p>Example: <code>18g in x 1:2 ratio = 36g out</code></p>

<h3>Time mode</h3>

<p><code>Time = (Dose x Ratio) / Flow + 16s</code></p>

<p>Example: <code>(18g x 2) / 1.8g/s + 16s = 36s</code></p>

<p>If you do not use a scale, time mode gives you a practical starting point, but the last phase duration may need to be adjusted for your real flow.</p>

<h2>Roast and ratio recommendations</h2>

<h3>Medium-dark roasts</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Around <code>91°C</code></li>
  <li>Ratio: <code>1:1.5</code> to <code>1:2.5</code></li>
  <li>Typical total shot time: about <code>36s</code></li>
</ul>

<h3>Medium-light roasts</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Around <code>94°C</code></li>
  <li>Ratio: <code>1:2.5</code> to <code>1:3+</code></li>
  <li>Typical total shot time: about <code>46s</code></li>
</ul>

{
  showCalculator && (
    <>
      <h2>Calculator</h2>

      <p>The current dose calculator remains external for now:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://automatic-pro-calculator.vercel.app/">Automatic Pro calculator</a>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>Use it when you want to adapt the core logic to a custom dose without manually recalculating every value.</p>
    </>
  )
}

<h2>After your first shot</h2>

<ul>
  <li>If the coffee tastes <strong>sour or salty</strong>, try a higher ratio like <code>1:2.5+</code> and consider a slightly higher temperature.</li>
  <li>If the coffee tastes <strong>bitter or dry</strong>, try a lower ratio like <code>1:1.5-</code> and consider a slightly lower temperature.</li>
  <li>
    If pressure looks too low or the basket has extra headspace, check <a href={`${base}troubleshooting/`}>Troubleshooting</a>.
  </li>
</ul>
